## 1Ô∏è‚É£ Font Suggestions (Safe + Professional)

### ‚úÖ Best Fonts for E-commerce (Google Fonts)

### üîπ **Poppins** (Highly Recommended)

* Clean
* Modern
* Great readability
* Looks good on buttons & headings

**Use for:** Headings + Buttons

```css
font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;
```

---

### üîπ **Inter** (Best for body text)

* Designed for screens
* Very readable
* Used by many modern apps

**Use for:** Paragraphs, product descriptions

```css
font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
```

---

### ‚≠ê Best Combo (Pro Choice)

```txt
Headings: Poppins
Body Text: Inter
```

This combo is extremely common in real e-commerce sites.

---

## 2Ô∏è‚É£ Typography Explained (Very Simple)

### What is Typography?

Typography = **how text looks and feels** on your website.

It includes:

* Font type
* Font size
* Font weight
* Spacing

Good typography = easy to read + looks premium.

---

## 3Ô∏è‚É£ Typography Basics You MUST Know

### üîπ Font Hierarchy (Most Important)

Not all text should look the same.

Example:

```txt
H1 ‚Üí Big & Bold (Hero heading)
H2 ‚Üí Section titles
H3 ‚Üí Product names
Body ‚Üí Descriptions
Small ‚Üí Price notes, labels
```

If everything is same size ‚Üí user gets confused.

---

### üîπ Font Weight

Controls thickness of text.

```txt
300 ‚Äì Light
400 ‚Äì Regular
500 ‚Äì Medium
600 ‚Äì Semi-bold
700 ‚Äì Bold
```

**Best practice**

* Headings: 600‚Äì700
* Body text: 400‚Äì500
* Buttons: 500‚Äì600

---

### üîπ Line Height (Huge for readability)

Too tight = bad
Too loose = messy

Best rule:

```css
line-height: 1.5;
```

---

### üîπ Font Size Guide (Desktop)

```txt
Hero Heading: 40‚Äì48px
Section Heading: 24‚Äì32px
Body Text: 16‚Äì18px
Buttons: 14‚Äì16px
```

Mobile ‚Üí slightly smaller.

---

## 4Ô∏è‚É£ Typography Golden Rules

‚úî Max **2 fonts only**
‚úî Keep body text simple
‚úî Use bold for emphasis, not color
‚úî Consistency everywhere

---

