## 1. Tailwind config: fonts & colors

**`tailwind.config.js`**

```js
/** @type {import('tailwindcss').Config} */
module.exports = {
  content: ["./src/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx,html}"],
  theme: {
    extend: {
      fontFamily: {
        sans: ["Inter", "system-ui", "sans-serif"],
        heading: ["Poppins", "system-ui", "sans-serif"],
        mono: ["JetBrains Mono", "monospace"],
      },
      colors: {
        brand: {
          50:  "#eef2ff",
          100: "#e0e7ff",
          500: "#6366f1", // primary
          600: "#4f46e5",
          700: "#4338ca",
        },
        neutral: {
          50:  "#fafafa",
          100: "#f5f5f5",
          400: "#a3a3a3",
          700: "#404040",
          900: "#171717",
        },
        success: "#16a34a",
        danger: "#dc2626",
      },
    },
  },
  plugins: [],
};
```

**Usage**

```html
<h1 class="font-heading text-brand-700">Title</h1>
<p class="font-sans text-neutral-700">Body text</p>
```

üí° Tip: keep **brand colors limited** (1 primary, 1 accent). Everything else should be neutral.

---

## 2. Button styles (primary vs secondary)

### Base button pattern

Create a reusable mental model:

```html
<button class="btn btn-primary">Primary</button>
<button class="btn btn-secondary">Secondary</button>
```

### Tailwind classes

```css
/* globals.css */
@layer components {
  .btn {
    @apply inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-md px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium
           transition-colors focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-offset-2;
  }

  .btn-primary {
    @apply bg-brand-600 text-white hover:bg-brand-700
           focus:ring-brand-600 disabled:bg-brand-300;
  }

  .btn-secondary {
    @apply bg-neutral-100 text-neutral-900 hover:bg-neutral-200
           focus:ring-neutral-400 disabled:text-neutral-400;
  }
}
```

**Design rules**

* **Primary**: main action per screen (1 max)
* **Secondary**: alternative or cancel action
* Avoid ‚Äúghost buttons‚Äù for critical actions on mobile

---

## 3. Mobile typography rules (this matters more than desktop)

### Font sizes (mobile-first)

```html
<h1 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-heading">Heading</h1>
<h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-heading">Subheading</h2>
<p class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed">
  Body text optimized for mobile readability
</p>
```

### Recommended scale (mobile)

| Type  | Size               |
| ----- | ------------------ |
| Body  | `text-base` (16px) |
| Small | `text-sm` (14px)   |
| H1    | `text-2xl` (24px)  |
| H2    | `text-xl` (20px)   |

**Rules of thumb**

* Never go below **14px** for body text
* Increase **line-height**, not font size, for readability
* Headings should be **shorter on mobile**

---

## 4. Accessibility tips (contrast & font size)

### Color contrast

* Text should meet **WCAG AA**

  * Normal text: **4.5:1**
  * Large text (‚â•18px or 14px bold): **3:1**
* Avoid:

  ```html
  text-neutral-400 on bg-white ‚ùå
  ```

Better:

```html
text-neutral-700 on bg-white ‚úÖ
```

### Focus states (don‚Äôt skip this)

```html
<button class="focus:ring-2 focus:ring-brand-600 focus:ring-offset-2">
```

### Touch targets (mobile!)

* Minimum **44√ó44px**

```html
<button class="min-h-[44px] px-4">
```

### Font accessibility

* Use **system fonts fallback**
* Avoid ultra-thin weights (`font-thin`)
* Prefer `font-medium` or `font-semibold` for buttons

---

## TL;DR design system rules

* **Fonts**: 1 body, 1 heading
* **Colors**: 1 brand color, neutrals do the heavy lifting
* **Buttons**: primary = rare & obvious
* **Mobile first**: 16px body, generous spacing
* **Accessibility**: contrast, focus rings, touch size

